name: 8 Out of 10 Cats
overview: 8 Out of 10 Cats is a British television comedy panel game produced by Zeppotron for Channel 4. It was first broadcast on 3 June 2005. The show is based on statistics and opinion polls, and draws on polls produced by a variety of organizations and new polls commissioned for the programme, carried out by company Harris Poll. The show's title is derived from a well-known advertising tagline for Whiskas cat food, which originally claimed that "8 out of 10 cats prefer Whiskas".

episodes.overview: The final show in the current series of 8 Out of 10 Cats brings debate, dispute and deliberation over the hot topics that are getting the almighty British public's chins wagging. As ever, presenter and stand up comic Jimmy Carr is in the host's chair and is joined by witty team captains Sean Lock and Jason Manford who are supported by celebrity guests: Carol Vorderman, Myleene Klass, Russell Kane and Rufus Hound.

episodes.name: Christmas Special - Jack Dee, Christopher Biggins, Josie Long, Lorraine Kelly
episodes.overview: Jimmy Carr hosts a Christmas edition of Channel 4's hit comedy panel show. Featuring special guests Jack Dee, Lorraine Kelly, Josie Long and Britain's favourite pantomime Dame, Christopher Biggins, the teams are led by captains Sean Lock and Jason Manford. Together they dispute and deliberate all things festive - from the best things about Christmas Day to the worst person to spend Christmas with. A mixture of surveys, statistics and opinion polls reveal what the nation thinks but do our celebrities agree?
